33:59.362 --> 34:10.796
However, if water from the rock was an image of Jesus that God wanted to preserve, do you see why there might have been greater significance to striking versus speaking to the rock?

34:12.417 --> 34:17.363
The judgment Christ bore for us was completed at Calvary.

34:18.965 --> 34:23.090
God's rod of judgment, judgment for our sins, struck.

34:24.354 --> 34:29.820
Jesus died and his final words were, it is finished.

34:31.102 --> 34:32.383
There's nothing more to be done.

34:34.706 --> 34:43.436
There are a lot of Bible students who think that there is great significance when John and his gospel records what happened after Jesus had died.

34:44.076 --> 34:47.420
You recall the Roman soldier that came to make sure that he was dead.

34:47.901 --> 34:52.626
John 1934, one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear

34:52.834 --> 34:56.358
and at once there came out blood and water.

34:57.800 --> 35:03.646
Now there are good medical reasons for that soldier to have seen what appeared to be a mix of blood and water.

35:03.747 --> 35:05.609
It's called pericardial effusion.

35:07.130 --> 35:15.180
The stress, the trauma Jesus had endured would have caused both blood and clear liquid would look like water to pool around the heart.

35:17.182 --> 35:20.626
But I think John also saw in that a greater spiritual reality.

35:21.954 --> 35:24.859
In Jesus' death, we are offered life.

35:26.061 --> 35:27.443
He was struck.

35:28.484 --> 35:31.529
His blood paid the price.

35:31.850 --> 35:36.658
And from him also came the spiritual water for our souls, the life that we needed.

35:37.960 --> 35:40.965
That spiritual life is something that we've drawn for all of life.

35:41.105 --> 35:44.370
It is available to us freely, simply for the asking.

35:46.146 --> 35:56.896
Remember the woman at the well, looking ahead to what he knew he was going to do at Calvary, Jesus told her that the living water she truly needed was available simply for the asking.

35:58.838 --> 36:06.906
In light of that, can you see why Moses choosing to disobey God's clear instruction might have been so offensive in God's eyes.

36:08.448 --> 36:10.550
