36:24.360 --> 36:25.302
Okay, string number one.

36:25.622 --> 36:26.303
String number two.

36:27.805 --> 36:29.607
What about those angry, thirsty people?

36:30.728 --> 36:38.538
I think it's a little easier to understand and show some grace to those folks the first time they got upset, that first time they encountered the rock out there in the wilderness.

36:39.219 --> 36:41.842
Thirst is the most basic driver

36:41.954 --> 36:55.655
of our human physical bodies and put thousands of people in a desert along with their livestock with no source of water in sight and no matter how many miracles they've seen, you can maybe cut them some slack for being a little anxious.

36:57.098 --> 37:10.098
What's harder to understand is how they could end up once again in the same situation and once again be on the verge of mutiny when they already had a proven history of God's provision in the very same kind of situation.

37:12.354 --> 37:16.398
But like I said earlier, we aren't so different.

37:16.418 --> 37:21.483
Here's a question I would pose, and you'll have to do some self-reflection, you and the Lord together.

37:23.765 --> 37:28.009
What are your affections in difficult times?

37:30.151 --> 37:38.119
