the salt water that we so easily turn toward.

45:20.260 --> 45:27.567
Things that offer the illusion that they will satisfy us, and yet we come up still thirsty.

45:30.089 --> 45:36.196
Lord, we receive your invitation this morning, the invitation to come and to drink of you.

45:38.678 --> 45:42.642
For any who have never come to that first rock, Lord, I pray that you would

45:42.754 --> 45:50.185
You'd awaken that thirst in them and help their eyes to see that in fact, there is life in you.

45:50.225 --> 46:00.781
For those of us who have received that life and yet as the years have gone on, we have allowed things to distract us and things to ensnare us.

46:01.662 --> 46:12.338
Father, help us, I pray, like that athlete to break free by your grace, by your power, to desire you, to meditate in your word,

46:12.738 --> 46:20.804
to lift our hearts to you in prayer, to once again find that you are all that our souls truly need.

46:22.991 --> 46:26.322
I pray this in Jesus' powerful name, amen.

